column5: Just like other posts said, the fish have been on all week. keep a few whitie's and laker and released a bunch more between two of us. Tons of bait fish, isolate the jigging spoon from the bait ball and they were rocketing through the bait clusters to attack the lone spoon.  Whitie's and a few lakers were on the Bad boy.  Good luck!! RF
nice going I hope to get out there this weekend
Nice work......how much fun is it out there when the fishing is on !!! Man, I just love it!!  Sinker
Great job on the lakers and whities.
Good work!  It was quite a day out there again today!   Not even time for pics lol!   Gotta love simcoe!
Except for the COLD hands from all the fish handling LOL....  RF
They'll be pigged out and stuffed by then...  they is workin fish!  9-5 mon.-fri.!!!  Sat and Sun., they're off!
yeah yeah story of my life

My hands are still burning!!!! We had our fun with the big  fish this morning, then headed in to the perch grounds.......caught 48 keepers between 2 of us......you want to talk about fish handling.......WOW.  At least its not -30 like last week!!!   Sinker
Do the whities/lakers stay pretty good through February?

man o man o man...these simcoe reports are killin' me...lol  those fish really are in the mood to bite at the monment...top stuff RF...its way to much fun, hopin' we get some action like that on Sunday.   Keep up the good work.
Great report and pics RF  Real nice looking whities and lakers.... Congratulations and thanks for sharing Leechman
Those Whities look nice!!!...congrats on a great day out on the ice
